article.headline: TCU 77, Wyoming 58
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Kevin Langford scored a career-high 24 points Wednesday night to lead TCU to a 77-58 victory over Wyoming. Langford hit 9-of-19 from the field, including 3-of-4 3-pointers, and three of his five free throws. Neiman Owens added 13 points. Brent Hackett scored 12 and Neil Dougherty added 11 for TCU (12-15, 4-11 Mountain West). Daaron Brown led Wyoming (15-14, 6-9) with 15 points. Eric Platt came off the bench to score 13. He also had two steals and a blocked shot. Brad Jones scored 11 points and had seven assists. TCU led 39-30 at halftime. TCU shot 48 percent from the field while Wyoming shot 43 percent.
